      • uploadDockerFiles

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> uploadDockerFiles(java.lang.String parentDirectoryName,
                                                          java.lang.String dirPath,
                                                          java.lang.String serverAddress,
                                                          java.lang.String portNumber)
        Uploads all docker files under given directory path recursively.
        Parameters:
        parentDirectoryName - The parent directory names. NOTE: just call with empty string "". Used for subsequent calls only!!!.
        dirPath - The path to the docker files to upload as String. Will be used as folder name on the server.
        serverAddress - The url or ip address as String WITHOUT "http://". (e.g. some.server.com)
        portNumber - The port number on which the server is listening as String. (e.g. "66666")
        Returns:
        List of Responses. (e.g. response.getStatus() +" : "+ response.readEntity(String.class)

        jarFile - the jar file
        tsdbName - the implementation name
        serverAddress - The http or ip address as String. (e.g. "http://some.server.com)
        portNumber - The port number on which the server is listening as String. (e.g. "66666")
